The rate of chikungunya seropositivity among patients from the eight provinces ranged from 9.18% in Khuzestan (28/305) to 23% in Ilam (23/100) (
 Fig. 1). The rate of dengue seropositivity among patients from the eight provinces ranged from 5.24% in Khuzestan (16/305) to 13.04% in Ilam (3/23) (
 Fig. 2). The highest rate of chikungunya seropositivity was found in Kerman, Fars and Ilam, and the highest rate of dengue seropositivity was found in Ilam, Fars and Khorasan-e-Jonubi. Logistic regression analysis showed a significant increase in the CHIKV IgM antibody seropositivity rate in Kerman (OR = 2.07, 95% CI: 1.10–3.92; 
 P = 0.024) and Fars (OR = 1.77, 95% CI: 1.06–2.93; 
 P = 0.027).
